{"blocks":[{"key":"1ca7e","text":"Hi everyone,","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8loq9","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5ukap","text":"Today I want to share my experience working with the NextJs framework. During the development of various projects, I encountered challenges that affected the performance of the application and overall user experience. I believe that my solutions to these problems are worth sharing with the community, especially those who are also working with NextJs.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"aqmvr","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"d4sn0","text":"As you may already know, NextJs is a powerful framework based on React that enables server-side rendering. This functionality brings impressive performance to platforms like our forum. However, like everything else, it comes with its set of challenges.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3pehl","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"58jgu","text":"Specifically, the problems I encountered were related to prefetching links and displaying new data (since all pages and requests are cached). In this post, we will focus on solving the first problem, while I will share the solution to the second problem in one of the future posts.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"63apr","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6fcir","text":"The main issue I noticed was that due to the large number of categories and links on each page of our platform, the default prefetching in NextJs was putting a strain on the server and causing significant CPU load during each initial site visit. Just imagine a scenario where 10,000 users visit the site simultaneously; the server would definitely struggle under such a load.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"15lj2","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"eqg5b","text":"I have been contemplating possible solutions to this problem. I didn't want to impose limitations on the backend because our system already has adequate security measures in place to prevent unauthorized access to our main API. Instead, I decided to create an open API using NodeJs to reduce the load on the main Laravel API.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7n83e","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"822bu","text":"But why NodeJs? NodeJs is designed to handle asynchronous operations, making it ideal for situations where you have a large number of concurrent requests. In our case, it helped alleviate the load on the Laravel API.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7ghr2","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"dnmqr","text":"NodeJs did a remarkable job. With its lower resource consumption and asynchronous requests, the Laravel API was relieved. However, I still believed there was room for improvement.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bai9f","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ett6p","text":"Although the NextJs Link component allows disabling prefetching, it wasn't an ideal solution as it would result in page reloading every time a link is clicked, which I personally didn't prefer.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4gbnv","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"54ao0","text":"So, what was my alternative?","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9mtvq","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6kc6p","text":"I created a new component that is similar to the default next/link component but with the addition that prefetching is only triggered when the user is ready to click on a specific link. This component provides a range of additional options for managing prefetching and navigation. I will describe these options and how the component works in detail below, and you can find the code for it at the end of this post.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ajjmc","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8amq5","text":"The component accepts the following properties:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8edfr","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5jkcd","text":"as: Defines the HTML attribute, default is <a>. You can define any other attribute.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"offset":0,"length":2,"style":"green"}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"a4f90","text":"noRedirect: If you don't want the user to be redirected to the specified link. This is useful for prefetching links if you want to perform prefetching in another component.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"offset":0,"length":10,"style":"green"}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4eiq7","text":"noPrefetch: If you don't want prefetching to be executed for a specific link.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"offset":0,"length":10,"style":"green"}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{